A 20-year-old man from Barry has died in a car crash in the early hours of Sunday.Two women, one aged 21 and also from Barry and an 18-year-old from Dinas Powys, Vale of Glamorgan, were taken to the University Hospital of Wales in Cardiff as a precaution.   The incident involved a a grey Ford Fiesta and occurred at around 03:50 BST on  the A4055 Barry Road in Dinas Powys.South Wales Police is appealing for any witnesses to the collision, or anyone with  dash-cam footage of the car being driven, to get in touch.
